	dprr:hasNoteText "Leg., lieut. Spain, ca. 40? (MRR 2.384). See below, on C. Livius L. f. Ocella (26).[125x]\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 8136 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6287> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6287" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Grant suggests that the C. Livius whose name appears on coins of Vesci in Baetica should be identified with the # named in Appian (BC 5.54), and was one of Octavian's Legates with L. Antonius in Spain (see above, Promagistrates, on L. Antonius, and on Cornelius Balbus; Grant, From Imperium to Auctoritas 379f.)." ;
	dprr:hasID 6287 .
